    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.8.5" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">5</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">ENOS A. MILLS
                        <lb/>
                    LONGS PEAK, COLORADO</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>June 12, 1921</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson, Nebr.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>My dear Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I would like to help boost much further the idea of honoring a worthy American poet while he is alive.</p>
                
                <p>In this connection have you any clippings you can spare me concerning the details which brought about the legislature of Nebraska honoring you as the Poet Laureate of that state? Who championed the idea?</p>
                
                <p>I possess the following books of yours. <title>The River and I</title>, <title>The Quest</title>, <title>The Song of Three Friends</title>, <title>The Song of Hugh Glass</title>, <title>The Splendid Wayfaring</title>, and I have also your biography by Mr. House.</p>
                
                <p>Have you copies that you could spare of <title>A Bundle of Myrrh</title>, <title>Man-Song</title> and any other books that you have issued? <del>f</del><add>I</add>f you have these, I wish you would kindly sign and send to me with the bill. If you have photographs of yourself, family and your new home I would be glad to have copies of them.</p> 
                
                <p>I do not know just what I shall do because I do not know just what is possible. But the idea I have mentioned in the opening of this letter has long seriously been in my mind.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>With best wishes,</salute>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Enos A. Mills</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="Neihardt">Is Mills one of our honorary members? I'm quite sure I gave his name lots of love always &#8212;John</note>
                
                <!-- on the side margins are the following notations, the first on the left, the second on the right.-->
                
                <note place="left margin" type="Neihardt">Does any suggestion occur to you as to how Mills might help? He has power. He wears the mantle of the late John Muir.</note>
                
                <note place="right margin" type="Neihardt">Bully stuff on "Wars"!</note>
                
            </div1>
